        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 26 at 6:49PM MDT until July 26 at 7:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Roosevelt County in northeastern Montana...
East central Valley County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern McCone County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 745 PM MDT.

* At 649 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near St. Marie, or
20 miles northeast of Glasgow, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Nashua, Lustre, St. Marie, and Volt.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
